160  /**
161   * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement}, mostly, if not exclusively, for use by {@link
162   * SyntheticAnnotationMirror} instances.
163   *
164   * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
165   * must not be {@code null}
166   *
167   * @param fullyQualifiedName the fully qualified name of the synthetic element; must conform to Java classname
168   * restrictions; must not be {@code null}
169   *
170   * @param elements a {@link List} of {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}s modeling the annotation elements; must not be
171   * {@code null}
172   *
173   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
174   *
175   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code fullyQualifiedName} does not conform to Java classname restrictions
176   *
177   * @see SyntheticAnnotationElement
178   *
179   * @see SyntheticAnnotationMirror
180   */
181  public SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
182                                        final SyntheticName fullyQualifiedName,
183                                        final List<? extends SyntheticAnnotationElement> elements) {
184    super();
185    this.annotationMirrors = List.copyOf(annotationMirrors);
186    final String fqn = fullyQualifiedName.toString();
187    final int i = fqn.lastIndexOf('.');
188    this.sn = i >= 0 ? new SyntheticName(fqn.substring(i + 1)) : fullyQualifiedName;
189    this.fqn = fullyQualifiedName;
190    this.type = new Type();
191    if (elements.isEmpty()) {
192      this.elements = List.of();
193    } else {
194      final List<InternalAnnotationElement> elements0 = new ArrayList<>(elements.size());
195      for (final SyntheticAnnotationElement e : elements) {
196        elements0.add(new InternalAnnotationElement(e.annotationMirrors(), e.type(), e.name(), e.defaultValue()));
197      }
198      this.elements = unmodifiableList(elements0);
199    }
200  }

295  // See https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1
296  private static final TypeMirror validateScalarType(final TypeMirror type) {
297    return switch (type) {
298    case null -> throw new NullPointerException("t");
299    case PrimitiveType t when t.getKind().isPrimitive() -> t;
300    case DeclaredType t when t.getKind() == DECLARED -> {
301      final TypeElement te = (TypeElement)t.asElement();
302      yield switch (te.getKind()) {
303      case ANNOTATION_TYPE, ENUM -> t;
304      default -> {
305        final Name fqn = te.getQualifiedName();
306        if (fqn.contentEquals("java.lang.Class") || fqn.contentEquals("java.lang.String")) {
307          yield t;
308        }
309        throw new IllegalArgumentException("type: " + type);
310      }
311      };
312    }
313    default -> throw new IllegalArgumentException("type: " + type);
314    };
315  }

429    /**
430     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
431     *
432     * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
433     * must not be {@code null}
434     *
435     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
436     * not be {@code null}
437     *
438     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
439     * {@code null}
440     *
441     * @param defaultValue a {@link SyntheticAnnotationValue} representing the default value; may be {@code null}
442     *
443     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
444     *
445     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
446     *
447     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
448     * section 9.6.1
449     */
450    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
451                                      final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
452                                      final SyntheticName name,
453                                      final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue) {
454      super();
455      this.annotationMirrors = List.copyOf(annotationMirrors);
456      this.type = switch (type) {
457      case null -> throw new NullPointerException("type");
458      case ArrayType t when t.getKind() == ARRAY -> validateScalarType(t.getComponentType());
459      default -> validateScalarType(type);
460      };
461      if (name.equals("getClass") || name.equals("hashCode") || name.equals("toString")) {
462        // java.lang.Object-declared methods that might otherwise meet annotation element requirements
463        throw new IllegalArgumentException("name: " + name);
464      }
465      this.name = name;
466      this.defaultValue = defaultValue;
467    }
468
469
470    /*
471     * Instance fields.
472     */
473
474
475    final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors() {
476      return this.annotationMirrors;
477    }
478
479    @Override // Object
480    public final boolean equals(final Object other) {
481      return this == other || switch (other) {
482      case null -> false;
483      case SyntheticAnnotationElement sae when this.getClass() == sae.getClass() ->
484      Objects.equals(this.name, sae.name) &&
485      Objects.equals(this.type, sae.type) &&
486      Objects.equals(this.annotationMirrors, sae.annotationMirrors); // TODO: hmm
487      default -> false;
488      };
489    }
490
491    @Override // Object
492    public final int hashCode() {
493      int hashCode = 31;
494      int c = this.name.hashCode();
495      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
496      c = this.type.hashCode();
497      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
498      c = this.annotationMirrors.hashCode(); // TODO: hmm
499      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
500      return hashCode;
501    }
502
503    final SyntheticName name() {
504      return this.name;
505    }
506
507    final TypeMirror type() {
508      return this.type;
509    }
510
511    final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue() {
512      return this.defaultValue;
513    }

729    private static final class Type implements ExecutableType {

731
732      /*
733       * Instance fields.
734       */

740      /*
741       * Constructors.

745      private Type(final TypeMirror type) { // the "return type"
746        super();
747        this.type = switch (type) {
748        case null -> throw new NullPointerException("type");
749        case ArrayType t when t.getKind() == ARRAY -> validateScalarType(t.getComponentType());

752      }
